<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Jose Mourinho was caught short last night as he found the goalposts were five centimetres too low before his Tottenham side’s 3-1 Europa League win over Shkendija of North Macedonia. </p>

<p>The goalkeepers noticed the flaw in the warm-up and alerted Mourinho, who said: ‘I am not a goalkeeper but when I spread my arms I know the difference.’ </p>

<p>Goals from Erik Lamela, Son Heung-min and Harry Kane sealed victory for Spurs, who will host Maccabi Haifa in the final play-off round next Thursday. </p>

<p>Jose Mourinho revealed he had to get UEFA delegates to switch the goals at KF Shkendija</p>
